wikipedia_page.main: Natalie Powell (born 16 October 1990) is a Welsh judoka. She competed for Wales in the women's 78 kg event at the 2014 Commonwealth Games where she won a gold medal. In 2017 she became the first female British judoka to be ranked number one in the world, which she accomplished by winning a gold medal at the Abu Dhabi judo Grand Slam 2017. Earlier that year she won a bronze medal at the European Championships.In May 2019, Powell was selected to compete at the 2019 European Games in Minsk, Belarus.In 2021, she competed in the women's 78 kg event at the 2020 Summer Olympics in Tokyo, Japan.She is openly lesbian and she is in a relationship with Sanne van Dijke from 2018.
